---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import CodeExample from '../../components/CodeExample.astro';

const playgroundExample = `.feature-panel {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-m);
}

.feature-panel > .title {
    margin: 0;
}

.feature-panel--highlighted {
    border-color: var(--colour-accent);
}`;

const stateExample = `.feature-panel.is_active {
    border-color: var(--colour-accent);
}`;
---

<DocsLayout
    title="LSCSS Playground"
    description="Experimenting with Layered Semantic CSS patterns."
>
    <section class="site-hero">
        <p class="eyebrow">Playground</p>

        <h1>
            Playground
        </h1>

        <p class="intro">
            A lab for testing component structure, naming, modifiers, state,
            scope, and layering without dragging a production codebase into the
            experiment.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-block">
        <h2>
            Start experimenting
        </h2>

        <div class="hub-card-grid">
            <article class="hub-card">
                <h3>
                    <a href="/playground/live-editor/">Live CSS editor</a>
                </h3>

                <p>
                    Edit CSS directly and see changes against a small component
                    example.
                </p>
            </article>

            <article class="hub-card">
                <h3>
                    <a href="/tools/specificity-calculator/">Specificity calculator</a>
                </h3>

                <p>
                    Test selector weight before you create an override problem
                    that follows the team home.
                </p>
            </article>

            <article class="hub-card">
                <h3>
                    <a href="/tools/scope-demo/">Scope demo</a>
                </h3>

                <p>
                    Compare scoped selectors with traditional component
                    selectors.
                </p>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-block">
        <h2>
            Basic component experiment
        </h2>

        <p>
            Start with one semantic parent component, short child classes, and
            one deliberate modifier.
        </p>

        <CodeExample code={playgroundExample} />
    </section>

    <section class="content-block">
        <h2>
            State experiment
        </h2>

        <p>
            Use state classes for temporary or conditional UI state. Do not turn
            every visual difference into a modifier.
        </p>

        <CodeExample code={stateExample} />
    </section>

    <section class="content-block">
        <h2>
            Try breaking it on purpose
        </h2>

        <ol>
            <li>Add one extra level of selector nesting.</li>
            <li>Add a modifier for something that is really temporary state.</li>
            <li>Add a utility class that duplicates component CSS.</li>
            <li>Move the component to the wrong layer.</li>
            <li>Fix each issue using the decision trees.</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="content-block">
        <h2>
            Useful next demos
        </h2>

        <div class="hub-card-grid">
            <article class="hub-card">
                <h3><a href="/tools/container-query-visualiser/">Container query visualiser</a></h3>
                <p>Test component responsiveness without relying on viewport assumptions.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="hub-card">
                <h3><a href="/tools/devtools-inspector/">DevTools-style inspector</a></h3>
                <p>Inspect how layers, selectors, and overrides work together.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="hub-card">
                <h3><a href="/decision-trees/">Decision trees</a></h3>
                <p>Use practical rules when a CSS choice stops being obvious.</p>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>
</DocsLayout>
